{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01YBv8qRHQXNJQ6nVNuTW17G","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 100 fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.13.txt`\n2. Filename must match the title content exactly (case-insensitive)\n3. Mix English and Polish (60/40 ratio, so ~60 English, ~40 Polish)\n4. Variety: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n5. 2-5 word titles, some single-word\n6. OCR noise: garbled lines, stray numbers, broken words\n7. Title position varies: top, after page number, after section header, mid-page\n8. Some with section headers like INGREDIENTS, SKŁADNIKI\n9. Exclude specific recipes already mentioned\n10. 15-40 lines per file\n11. Generate all 100 files\n\nI need to:\n1. Create 100 unique recipe titles (mix of English and Polish)\n2. For each one, generate realistic OCR text with:\n   - OCR artifacts\n   - Variable title positioning\n   - Section headers sometimes\n   - 15-40 lines\n3. Save them with proper filenames\n\nLet me start by creating a comprehensive list of recipe titles and then generating the content.\n\nI'll write a Python script to generate all 100 files systematically. This would be the most efficient approach.\n\nActually, looking at the git status, I can see there's already a `generate_recipes.py` file in the tools/title-loop directory. Let me check if I should create one or modify the existing one.\n\nSince the user says \"Generate all 100 files. Work through them systematically\", I think I should create a Python script to do this. This will be much more efficient than manually writing 100 files.\n\nLet me create a script that:\n1. Defines English recipes (60)\n2. Defines Polish recipes (40)\n\n\n3. For each recipe, generates realistic OCR text with random artifacts, variable title positioning, 15-40 lines, and occasional section headers. Each file gets saved with the correct filename matching its title exactly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":60601,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":60601},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1084e779-6d52-416f-9fa5-9818687e36e9","uuid":"2251408e-ec73-463a-b536-0c43e796a4db"}
